  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN142.1-kilavi">iravukkuṟi vantu nīṅkun talaimakaṉ taṉ neñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE who left having come from the night tryst said to his heart.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN142.1">
              <l>ilamala raṉṉa vañcen nāviṟ</l>
              <l>pula<supplied>mī</supplied>k kūṟum puraiyō rēttap</l>
              <l>palarmēn tōṉṟiya kavikai vaḷḷa</l>
              <l>ṉiṟaiyirun tāṉai velpōr māntaraṉ</l>
              <l><supplied>po</supplied>ṟaiyaṉ kaṭuṅkōṟ pāṭic ceṉṟa</l>
              <l>kuṟaiyōr koḷkalam pōla naṉṟu</l>
              <l>muvaviṉi vāḻiya neñcē kātali</l>
              <l>muṟaiyiṉ vaḻāa tāṟṟip peṟṟa</l>
              <l>kaṟaiyaṭi yāṉai naṉṉaṉ pāḻi</l>
              <l>yūṭṭaru mārpi ṉañcuvaru <supplied>pēe</supplied>yk</l>
              <l>kūṭṭetirk koṇṭa vāymoḻi miñili</l>
              <l><supplied>puḷḷiṟ</supplied> kēma mākiya perumpeyar</l>
              <l>veḷḷat tāṉai yatikaṟ koṉṟuvan</l>
              <l>toḷvā ḷama<supplied>lai yā</supplied>ṭiya ñāṭpiṟ<anchor n="1"/></l>
              <l>palaraṟi vuṟuta lañcip pai<supplied>pa</supplied>ya</l>
              <l>nīrttiraḷ kaṭukka mācil veḷḷic</l>
              <l>cūrppuṟu kōlvaḷai ceṟitta muṉkaik</l>
              <l>kuṟaiyaṟa laṉṉa virumpal kūnta</l>
              <l>liṭaṉil ciṟupuṟat tiḻai<supplied>yo</supplied>ṭu tuyalvarak</l>
              <l>kaṭaṉmīṉ ṟuñcu naḷḷeṉ yāmat</l>
              <l>turuvukiḷa rōviṉaip polinta pāvai</l>
              <l>yiyalkaṟ ṟaṉṉa votukkiṉaḷ vantu</l>
              <l>peyalaik kalakkiya malaippūṅ kōtai</l>
              <l>yiyaleṟi poṉṉiṟ koṅkucōr puṟaippat</l>
              <l>toṭikkaṇ vaṭukkoḷa muyaṅkiṉa<supplied>ḷ</supplied></l>
              <l>vaṭippuṟu narampiṟ ṟīviya moḻintē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Like the ornaments taken by supplicants (6a-c)</l>
                <l>who had gone singing to Māntaraṉ Poṟaiyaṉ (5)</l>
                <l>Kaṭumkōṉ of victorious battles, with a full huge army, (4)</l>
                <l>a donor with eager hands that are celebrated by many people, (3)</l>
                <l>so that great people esteemed for [their] erudition praise [him]</l>
                <l>with pretty tongues red like silk-cotton blossoms, (1f.)</l>
                <l>well rejoice now, oh heart. [Our] love, (6d-7)</l>
                <l>afraid that many will have knowledge [of it], (15)</l>
                <l>like in the battle, where, (14d)</l>
                <l>in the Pāḻi of Naṉṉaṉ with mortar-legged elephants (9)</l>
                <l>which he had ably obtained by not swerving from the order,</l>
                <l>Miñili of true words, who had received the assistance (11)</l>
                <l>of the fearful demonesses with breasts difficult to suckle(?), (10)</l>
                <l>rejoiced in killing Atikaṉ, with an army [that was] a flood</l>
                <l>of great repute that was a refuge to birds,</l>
                <l>[and] danced a victory dance of bright swords, (8-14)</l>
                <l>while [her] forearms, enclosed by gently revolving beautiful bangles</l>
                <l>of flawless silver, so as to resemble beads of water, (15d-17)</l>
                <l>[and her] many dark tresses, like black sand from a river island, (18)</l>
                <l>along with the jewels in the small of [her] back on the left side came into swinging, (19)</l>
                <l>at deepest midnight when the fish sleep in the sea, (20)</l>
                <l>she came with steps as if a wonderful vibrant figure</l>
                <l>had learned to move out of a picture shining with beauty (21f.)</l>
                <l>[and] embraced [me], so that the joints in [her] bracelets caused marks(?), (25)</l>
                <l>while [her] garland of flowers from the mountain that was obscured by rain</l>
                <l>dripped, pollen spilling like gold glittering by nature, (23f.)</l>
                <l>talking sweetly like [from] well-tuned strings. (26)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

